ce:section.ce:para:
Food safety always is an attracted problem in the world. In Europe, the USA and China, FZD is forbidden in foods. To verify the applicability and reliability of method for sensing FZD by N, S, B doped CNDs and CNDs@MIPs in real samples, chicken feed, honey and pork were detected by standard addition method. FZD was not detected in the three food residues using N, S, B doped CNDs and CNDs@MIPs, indicating that these foods conformed to the food policy. The recoveries were 90.79%–109.53% in the standard recovery tests for the N, S, B doped CNDs (Table 1
                        ). In the meantime, the recoveries were 90.79%–109.94% for the CNDs@MIPs and the relative standard deviation (RSD) was less than 3.7% (n = 3), and the red fluorescence intensity ratios were approximately 1.00 before and after adding FZD (Table 2
                        ). The excellent results demonstrated that the proposed methodology based on N, S, B doped CNDs and CNDs@MIPs was reliable and applicable for sensing FZD in real samples.
